title: José Luis Rodríguez Zapatero - Wikipedia
snippet: José Luis Rodríguez Zapatero (Spanish: [xoseˈlwis roˈðɾiɣeθ θapaˈteɾo] ⓘ; born 4 August 1960) is a Spanish politician and member of the Spanish Socialist Workers' Party (PSOE). He was the Prime Minister of Spain being elected for two terms, in the 2004 and 2008 general elections.

title: José Luis Rodríguez Zapatero | Spanish PM, Socialist Leader | Britannica
snippet: José Luis Rodríguez Zapatero (born August 4, 1960, Valladolid, Spain) is a Spanish politician, who served as prime minister of Spain from 2004 to 2011.

title: José Luis Rodríguez Zapatero – International Commission against the Death Penalty
snippet: José Luis Rodríguez Zapatero was Prime Minister of Spain from 2004 to 2011. Mr. Zapatero has a law degree from the University of Leon, Spain. He was later appointed Professor of Constitutional Law at the same university.

title: José Luis Rodríguez Zapatero | World Leaders Forum
snippet: José Luis Rodríguez Zapatero is president of the government of Spain. Born in 1960, he has a degree in law from the University of Léon. He has been a member of the Spanish Socialists’ Party (PSOE) since 1979. He is the secretary-general of the PSOE and since 2000.
